Yardi Systems has primarily grown through organic expansion and strategic acquisitions, with limited external funding; it remains privately owned and is led by its founder, Anant Yardi, who serves as CEO and President[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yardi_Systems][https://www.yardi.com/company/leadership-team/][https://www.yardi.com/company/about-us/]. The company’s ownership structure is closely held, with no evidence of public trading or significant outside investment beyond a single disclosed funding round in 2000[https://app.dealroom.co/companies/yardi_systems].

**Funding History:**
- Yardi Systems was founded in 1984 by Anant Yardi in Santa Barbara, California[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yardi_Systems][https://www.yardi.com/company/leadership-team/][https://www.yardi.com/company/about-us/].
- The only publicly documented funding round occurred in August 2000, when Yardi raised $35 million in a Series B round from investors including CBRE Group, CenterPoint Venture Partners, JLL, and Sevin Rosen Funds[https://app.dealroom.co/companies/yardi_systems].
- There is no record of subsequent venture capital or private equity funding, nor any indication that Yardi has gone public or raised additional rounds since 2000[https://app.dealroom.co/companies/yardi_systems].
- Yardi’s growth has been driven by reinvestment of operating profits and strategic acquisitions, such as PropertyShark in 2010 and a 60% equity stake in WeWork in 2024[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yardi_Systems].

**Current Ownership Structure:**
- Yardi Systems is a privately held company, with ownership concentrated among its founder, Anant Yardi, and possibly his family or close associates[https://www.yardi.com/company/leadership-team/][https://www.yardi.com/company/about-us/].
- Anant Yardi remains the CEO and President, actively leading the company’s strategic direction and product innovation[https://www.yardi.com/company/leadership-team/].
- There is no evidence of public shareholders or significant institutional ownership; the company is not listed on any stock exchange[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yardi_Systems][https://www.yardi.com/company/leadership-team/][https://www.yardi.com/company/about-us/].
- The leadership team is composed of long-tenured executives, further suggesting a stable, founder-led ownership structure[https://www.yardi.com/company/leadership-team/].

**Additional Context:**
- Yardi Systems employs over 9,000 professionals in more than 40 offices worldwide, reflecting its substantial organic growth since inception[https://www.yardi.com/company/about-us/].
- The company’s business model centers on providing subscription-based software solutions for real estate management, with revenues generated from software licensing and support services[https://app.dealroom.co/companies/yardi_systems][https://www.yardi.com/suite/investment-suite/].
- Yardi’s acquisition strategy has focused on expanding its product suite and market reach, rather than raising capital for liquidity or ownership changes[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yardi_Systems].

In summary, Yardi Systems is a privately owned, founder-led workplace management company with minimal external funding history and a tightly held ownership structure centered around Anant Yardi[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yardi_Systems][https://www.yardi.com/company/leadership-team/][https://app.dealroom.co/companies/yardi_systems][https://www.yardi.com/company/about-us/].

Lessen, a workplace and property management company, has undergone significant funding events and structural changes, particularly with its acquisition of SMS Assist in 2023. The company is currently led by founder and CEO Jay McKee, who also serves as Chairman of the Board[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist][https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-ceo-jay-mckee-one-year-after-proptechs-biggest-acquisition].

**Funding History:**
- In January 2023, Lessen acquired SMS Assist in a transaction valued at approximately **$950 million**[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-ceo-jay-mckee-one-year-after-proptechs-biggest-acquisition]. This deal was structured with a combination of cash, new equity, and debt financing, as well as SMS Assist stockholders exchanging a portion of their shares for Lessen stock[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist][https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-ceo-jay-mckee-one-year-after-proptechs-biggest-acquisition].
- The acquisition was backed by a syndicate of **debt and equity investors**, including Monroe Capital, Värde Partners, and Koch Real Estate Investments[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist]. In addition, some of Lessen’s clients, such as American Homes 4 Rent, also participated as investors in the deal[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist].
- The combined company’s **enterprise value** post-transaction was reported to be **over $2 billion**[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist][https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-ceo-jay-mckee-one-year-after-proptechs-biggest-acquisition].

**Ownership Structure:**
- After the acquisition, **Jay McKee** remains the CEO and Chairman, leading the combined entity[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist][https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-ceo-jay-mckee-one-year-after-proptechs-biggest-acquisition].
- **SMS Assist stockholders** became shareholders in the new, merged company by exchanging a portion of their SMS stock for Lessen stock[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist].
- **Institutional investors** (Monroe Capital, Värde Partners, Koch Real Estate Investments) and certain large clients (such as American Homes 4 Rent) hold equity stakes as a result of their participation in the funding round that enabled the acquisition[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist].
- The company is privately held, with ownership distributed among the founder, management, legacy SMS Assist shareholders, and the aforementioned institutional and client investors[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist][https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-ceo-jay-mckee-one-year-after-proptechs-biggest-acquisition].

**Additional Context:**
- The acquisition created one of the largest tech-enabled property services platforms in North America, serving both residential and retail real estate owners and vendors[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-ceo-jay-mckee-one-year-after-proptechs-biggest-acquisition].
- The company continues to operate under the Lessen brand, with Jay McKee at the helm, and has expanded its operations across the U.S. and Canada[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-ceo-jay-mckee-one-year-after-proptechs-biggest-acquisition][https://www.lessen.com].

In summary, Lessen’s funding history is defined by its major 2023 acquisition of SMS Assist, financed by a mix of debt, equity, and stock exchange, resulting in a diversified ownership structure led by its founder and supported by institutional and strategic investors[https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-acquires-sms-assist][https://www.lessen.com/resources/lessen-ceo-jay-mckee-one-year-after-proptechs-biggest-acquisition].

**Esusu**, a workplace and renter financial management company, has raised a total of **$140 million** across two major funding rounds and is currently **Black-owned**, led by its co-founders Wemimo Abbey and Samir Goel[https://esusurent.com/blog/esusu-raises-130-million-series-b/][https://www.zoominfo.com/c/esusu-financial-inc/453250421][https://techcrunch.com/2022/01/27/esusu-becomes-unicorn-with-softbank-vision-fund-2-led-130m-funding/][https://sixthstreet.com/podcasts/wemimo-abbey-co-founder-and-co-ceo-of-esusu/][https://esusurent.com/about/].

- **Series A:** In July 2021, Esusu raised **$10 million** in a Series A round led by Motley Fool Ventures. Other participants included Concrete Rose Capital, The Equity Alliance, Impact America Fund, Next Play Ventures, Serena Ventures, Sinai Ventures, and TypeOne Ventures[https://esusurent.com/blog/esusu-raises-130-million-series-b/][https://techcrunch.com/2022/01/27/esusu-becomes-unicorn-with-softbank-vision-fund-2-led-130m-funding/].
- **Series B:** In January 2022, Esusu closed a **$130 million Series B** round at a **$1 billion valuation**, led by SoftBank Vision Fund 2. Existing investors from the Series A round also participated in this round[https://esusurent.com/blog/esusu-raises-130-million-series-b/][https://techcrunch.com/2022/01/27/esusu-becomes-unicorn-with-softbank-vision-fund-2-led-130m-funding/][https://sixthstreet.com/podcasts/wemimo-abbey-co-founder-and-co-ceo-of-esusu/].
- **Total Funding:** The company’s total disclosed funding is **over $140 million**[https://www.zoominfo.com/c/esusu-financial-inc/453250421][https://techcrunch.com/2022/01/27/esusu-becomes-unicorn-with-softbank-vision-fund-2-led-130m-funding/].

**Current Ownership Structure:**

Domuso, a privately held workplace management and rent payment platform headquartered in Santa Monica, California, has raised a **total of approximately $5.7 million in funding across three rounds**, with the most recent round being under $5 million[https://www.zoominfo.com/c/domuso-inc/385486987]. Additionally, Domuso received an SBA PPP loan in the range of $350,000 to $1 million from Manufacturers Bank[https://www.zoominfo.com/c/domuso-inc/385486987].

Domuso was **co-founded by Michael Lightfoot and Damian Langere**[https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/]. The company is closely associated with several real estate and venture entities, including **GELT, GELT VE, Skya Ventures, Happy Home Communities, and Alpha Bridge Ventures**[https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/]. Notably, GELT Inc.—a real estate investment company—owns a significant portion of the properties managed through Domuso’s platform, with reports indicating that out of over 30,000 properties on Domuso, about 7,000 are owned by GELT Inc.[https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/]. This suggests a strong operational and ownership link between Domuso and GELT Inc.

**David Kim**, a founding member of the Bascom Group, is cited as the main investor in Domuso Inc.[https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/]. The Bascom Group is a well-known real estate investment firm, and Kim’s involvement points to substantial institutional backing.

Domuso’s **ownership structure** is therefore characterized by:
- **Private ownership**, with key founders Michael Lightfoot and Damian Langere[https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/].
- **Major investment and operational ties to GELT Inc.**, which owns a large share of the properties managed on Domuso’s platform[https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/].
- **David Kim (Bascom Group)** as a principal investor[https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/].
- **Associations with other real estate and venture entities**: GELT VE, Skya Ventures, Happy Home Communities, Alpha Bridge Ventures[https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/].

The company remains privately held and does not appear to have undergone acquisition or public offering as of the latest available information[https://www.zoominfo.com/c/domuso-inc/385486987][https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/]. Its leadership includes a CEO and CFO, but specific names beyond the founders are not detailed in the available sources[https://www.zoominfo.com/c/domuso-inc/385486987].

In summary:
- **Funding history:** ~$5.7M total, most recent round <$5M, plus PPP loan[https://www.zoominfo.com/c/domuso-inc/385486987].
- **Ownership structure:** Privately held; founders Michael Lightfoot and Damian Langere; major investor David Kim (Bascom Group); strong ties to GELT Inc. and related entities[https://liberationnews.org/california-housing-crisis-and-domusos-predatory-lending/][https://www.zoominfo.com/c/domuso-inc/385486987].
